               <head>Two Naqshbandi works</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85129649">
                  <summary>1 copy of Ḥasanāt al-ḥaramayn by Muḥammad Shākir ibn Shaykh Badr al-Dīn Sirhindī; 1 copy of Zubdat al-maqāmāt by Badakhshānī, Muḥammad Hāshim ibn Muḥammad Qāsim, active 1621-1646</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh85089070" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_994-item1">
                     <locus from="1" to="40">ff. 1-40</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Ḥasanāt al-ḥaramayn, a Persian translation by Muḥammad Shākir ibn Shaykh Badr al-Dīn Aḥmadī Sirhindī of the account (originally written in Arabic) of a journey to Mecca and Medina in 1068 (1657-58) by Khvājah 
                <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_220986160" role="aut">Muḥammad Maʻṣūm</persName>. The translation was completed in 1071 (1660-61) and provides a pious account of pilgrimage ceremonial. The work consists of three chapters and a khātimah.
                        </p>
                        <p>13 lines to a page; fair taʻliq; rubrications; ruled margins.</p>
                        <p>Dated 25 Shaʻbān 1075 (13 March 1665).</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f8021" type="supplied">Muḥammad Shākir ibn Shaykh Badr al-Dīn Sirhindī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="person_f8021">محمد شاکر بن شیخ بدر الدین سرهندی</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21823">Ḥasanāt al-ḥaramayn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_21823">حسنات الحرمین</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010115021 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85089073 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85089787" n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_994-item2">
                     <locus from="41" to="280">ff. 41-280</locus>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100167544701.0x000001 viaf_60710956" type="standard">Badakhshānī, Muḥammad Hāshim ibn Muḥammad Qāsim, active 1621-1646</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_60710956">بدخشانی، محمد هاشم بن محمد قاسم</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21825">Zubdat al-maqāmāt</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_21825">زبدة المقامات</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Zubdat al-maqāmāt, a record by Muḥammad al-Ḥāshim (fl. 1621-1646) of the sayings of the Naqshbandi Shaykhs: 
                <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_32839461" role="aut">Badr al-Dīn Abū al-Barakāt Aḥmad Fārūqī Sirhindī</persName>(1563-1624) and 
                <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_314814912" role="aut">Khvājah Muḥammad al-Bāqī al-Uvaysī al-Naqshbandī</persName>
                           . The author had met Shaykh Aḥmad Sirhindī in 1031(1621) and studied with him for nearly two years until his death. He compiled this record of their father's discourses including also those of Khvājah Muḥammad al-Bāqī at the request of the saint's sons. The work was completed, according to the final chronogram, in 1037 (1627).
                        </p>
                        <p>Lacuna after folio 49 and leaves apparently misplaced; 15-18 lines per page; small taʻliq in more than one hand; copyist (f. 90 to end) 
                <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f8015" role="scr">Nūr Allāh Sirhindī</persName>, a disciple of the author; rubrications; ruled margins.
                        </p>
                        <p>17th century</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note/>
